      "content": [
        {
          "text": "The Evolution of Artificial Intelligence in Modern Society",
          "type": "text"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "Artificial intelligence (AI) has rapidly transitioned from a theoretical discipline(Nils J. Nilsson, 1996) to a core component of modern technological infrastructure ",
          "type": "text"
        },
        {
          "text": "[1]",
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "citation-highlight",
              "attrs": {
                "type": "Style Rule",
                "color": "amber",
                "ruleId": "APA_INVALID_NUMERIC",
                "message": "APA style requires parenthetical citations (Author, Year), not numeric brackets.",
                "expected": "(Author, Year)",
                "badgeCode": "STY",
                "similarity": 0,
                "aiProbability": 0
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": ". Early conceptual models proposed by Turing laid the groundwork for what would later become machine intelligence (Turing, 19244).",
          "type": "text"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "In recent decades, AI systems have been integrated into healthcare, finance, transportation, and governance. According to Smith¹, diagnostic algorithms now outperform human clinicians in several narrowly defined tasks. These developments have raised ethical and regulatory concerns that must be addressed systematically.(Stuart Russell et al., 1995)",
          "type": "text"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "Several scholars argue that the adoption of AI must be guided by transparent policy frameworks (Johnson 45). However, others contend that excessive regulation may stifle innovation (Brown, 2019).",
          "type": "text"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "horizontalRule"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 2,
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "[1]",
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "citation-highlight",
              "attrs": {
                "type": "Style Rule",
                "color": "amber",
                "ruleId": "APA_INVALID_NUMERIC",
                "message": "APA style requires parenthetical citations (Author, Year), not numeric brackets.",
                "expected": "(Author, Year)",
                "badgeCode": "STY",
                "similarity": 0,
                "aiProbability": 0
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Artificial Intelligence in Healthcare",
          "type": "text"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "The healthcare sector has been one of the most aggressive adopters of AI-based tools. Clinical decision support systems are now used extensively in radiology, oncology, and pathology ",
          "type": "text"
        },
        {
          "text": "[2]",
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "citation-highlight",
              "attrs": {
                "type": "Style Rule",
                "color": "amber",
                "ruleId": "APA_INVALID_NUMERIC",
                "message": "APA style requires parenthetical citations (Author, Year), not numeric brackets.",
                "expected": "(Author, Year)",
                "badgeCode": "STY",
                "similarity": 0,
                "aiProbability": 0
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": ". Studies conducted in Europe suggest a statistically significant improvement in patient outcomes (Müller, 2021).",
          "type": "text"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "In one large-scale study, researchers demonstrated that convolutional neural networks could identify malignant  with an accuracy exceeding 94%¹. Similar findings were reported in a longitudinal analysis conducted across five hospitals (Lee et al., 2020).",
          "type": "text"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "Despite these advancements, ethical challenges remain unresolved. The question of accountability in algorithmic decision-making has been widely debated in academic literature ",
          "type": "text"
        },
        {
          "text": "[3]",
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "citation-highlight",
              "attrs": {
                "type": "Style Rule",
                "color": "amber",
                "ruleId": "APA_INVALID_NUMERIC",
                "message": "APA style requires parenthetical citations (Author, Year), not numeric brackets.",
                "expected": "(Author, Year)",
                "badgeCode": "STY",
                "similarity": 0,
                "aiProbability": 0
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": ".",
          "type": "text"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "horizontalRule"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 2,
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "Ethical and Social Implications",
          "type": "text"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "Ethical considerations surrounding AI extend beyond healthcare. Surveillance systems powered by facial recognition technology have raised concerns regarding privacy and civil liberties (Garcia, 2018). According to recent policy analyses, such systems may disproportionately affect marginalized populations¹.",
          "type": "text"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "Some ethicists advocate for a precautionary approach, emphasizing the importance of human oversight in automated systems (Williams 112). Others argue that technological neutrality should be preserved, allowing innovation to proceed without excessive moral constraints ",
          "type": "text"
        },
        {
          "text": "[4]",
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "citation-highlight",
              "attrs": {
                "type": "Style Rule",
                "color": "amber",
                "ruleId": "APA_INVALID_NUMERIC",
                "message": "APA style requires parenthetical citations (Author, Year), not numeric brackets.",
                "expected": "(Author, Year)",
                "badgeCode": "STY",
                "similarity": 0,
                "aiProbability": 0
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": ".",
          "type": "text"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "horizontalRule"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 2,
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "Governance and Regulation of AI Systems",
          "type": "text"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "Governments worldwide have begun implementing regulatory frameworks aimed at controlling the deployment of AI technologies. The European Union’s Artificial Intelligence Act represents one of the most comprehensive legislative efforts to date (European Commission, 2021).",
          "type": "text"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "In contrast, regulatory approaches in the United States remain fragmented, with oversight distributed across multiple agencies ",
          "type": "text"
        },
        {
          "text": "[5]",
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "citation-highlight",
              "attrs": {
                "type": "Style Rule",
                "color": "amber",
                "ruleId": "APA_INVALID_NUMERIC",
                "message": "APA style requires parenthetical citations (Author, Year), not numeric brackets.",
                "expected": "(Author, Year)",
                "badgeCode": "STY",
                "similarity": 0,
                "aiProbability": 0
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": ". Scholars note that this lack of coordination may hinder effective governance (Anderson, 2022).",
          "type": "text"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "horizontalRule"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 2,
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "Conclusion",
          "type": "text"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "Artificial intelligence continues to reshape multiple dimensions of human society. While its benefits are undeniable, the ethical, legal, and social challenges it presents require careful consideration. Future research must prioritize interdisciplinary collaboration to ensure that AI systems are developed and deployed responsibly (Smith 88).",
          "type": "text"
        }
      ]
    },
